As required, ``[a] DoD reference document, such as a STIG or SRG, constitutes
the primary source for security configuration or implementation guidance.'' The
policy (\S\ref{Policy}) configures AFSEO non-Windows hosts, and the procedures
(\S\ref{Procedures} and~\S\ref{ProceduresForUsers}) guide administrators and
users, according to these DISA-released documents:

\begin{itemize}
\item the UNIX SRG \cite{unix-srg} (see in particular~\S\ref{UNIXSRGCompliance} and~\S\ref{UNIXSTIGIndex})
\item the SPAN STIG \cite{span-stig} (see in particular~\S\ref{SPANSTIGCompliance} and~\S\ref{SPANSTIGIndex})
\item the Apache 2.2 Web Server and Web Site STIGs \cite{apache-server-stig}~\cite{apache-site-stig} (see~\S\ref{ApacheSTIGIndex})
\item the Generic Database STIG \cite{database-stig} (see in particular~\S\ref{DatabaseSTIGCompliance} and~\S\ref{DatabaseSTIGIndex})
\end{itemize}

See the Bibliography (\S\ref{Bibliography}) for the exact versions of these documents used.
